  "prompt": "How can I use psiphon on Macbook?",
  "response": "Psiphon is a circumvention tool that allows users to access blocked or censored websites. While Psiphon is primarily designed for Windows and Android, you can still use it on a MacBook by following these steps:\n\n---\n\n### **Option 1: Use Psiphon3 on Mac via Wine**\nPsiphon3 is a Windows application, but you can run it on macOS using **Wine**, a compatibility layer that allows Windows applications to run on Unix-like operating systems.\n\n1. **Install Wine:**\n   - Open **Terminal** and enter the following command to install Wine using Homebrew:\n     ```bash\n     brew install wine\n     ```\n   - If you don\u2019t have Homebrew installed, first install it by running:\n     ```bash\n     /bin/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)\"\n     ```\n\n2. **Download Psiphon3:**\n   - Visit the official Psiphon website: [https://psiphon.ca](https://psiphon.ca).\n   - Download the Windows version of Psiphon3 (e.g., `psiphon3.exe`).\n\n3. **Run Psiphon3 using Wine:**\n   - Open **Terminal** and navigate to the directory where `psiphon3.exe` is saved.\n   - Run the following command to launch Psiphon:\n     ```bash\n     wine psiphon3.exe\n     ```\n\n---\n\n### **Option 2: Use Psiphon Browser**\nPsiphon also offers a browser-based version that works on macOS.\n\n1. **Download Psiphon Browser:**\n   - Visit the official Psiphon website: [https://psiphon.ca](https://psiphon.ca).\n   - Scroll down to the **Psiphon Browser** section and download the macOS version.\n\n2. **Install and Run Psiphon Browser:**\n   - Once downloaded, open the `.dmg` file and drag the Psiphon Browser application to your **Applications** folder.\n   - Launch the Psiphon Browser from Applications.\n\n3. **Connect to Psiphon:**\n   - The Psiphon Browser will automatically connect to a secure server, allowing you to bypass censorship.\n\n---\n\n### **Option 3: Use Psiphon Pro with a VPN**\nPsiphon Pro is another option available on the macOS App Store.\n\n1. **Download Psiphon Pro:**\n   - Open the **App Store** on your MacBook.\n   - Search for **Psiphon Pro** and download the app.\n\n2. **Run Psiphon Pro:**\n   - Launch Psiphon Pro and follow the on-screen instructions to connect.\n\n---\n\n### **Option 4: Use Psiphon via Command Line**\nIf you prefer using the command line, you can run Psiphon via **Docker**.\n\n1. **Install Docker:**\n   - Download and install Docker for macOS from [https://www.docker.com](https://www.docker.com).\n\n2. **Run Psiphon in Docker:**\n   - Open **Terminal** and run the following command to pull and run the Psiphon Docker image:\n     ```bash\n     docker run -d --name psiphon psiphoncircumvention/psiphon\n     ```\n   - Access Psiphon by configuring your browser to use the Docker container as a proxy.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips:**\n- Ensure you have a stable internet connection before using Psiphon.\n- If you encounter issues, try restarting the application or switching to a different server.\n- Psiphon is free to use, but you may encounter ads in certain versions.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
